The MBA for Entrepreneurs

  1. 01

    Strategy &Innovation
    11 modules
    20 lessons

    This introductory module dives into the core principles that guide decision-making and problem-solving in the startup world.

    This module covers

    • The Problem-Oriented Mindset

    • Steve Blanks Value Proposition Formula

    • Assessing Market Opportunities

    • Market Sizing: Wazes Qualification Matrix

    • Picking the right Business Model

    • The Customer-Centric Approach

    • The Customer Discovery Journey: Lessons from Airbnb and Netflix

    • Wazes Customer Segmentation Framework

    • The Product Adoption Curve

  2. 02

    Entrepreneurship
    8 modules
    20 lessons

    Adopting an entrepreneurial mindset is key to success at all stages of business. The module brings you insights into how the worlds most brilliant entrepreneurs spot ideas, find customers and scale businesses.

    This module covers:


    • The Entrepreneurial Mindset

    • The Three Ingredients of a Business Idea

    • Building an Minimum Viable Product

    • Blue Ocean vs. Red Ocean Markets

    • Learning from Failure

    • Go-To Market Strategies

    • Picking the right Co-Founders

    • Competing with Giants: How Wikipedia beat Google

    • The Art of Pivoting

    • Bootstrapping vs. Raising Funds

    • Fighting Resistance: Lessons from Shazam.

  3. 03

    Leadership
    13 modules
    15 lessons

    Learn how to build strong team from those lead some of the worlds most successful entrepreneurs.

    This module covers:


    • Setting stretch goals: the OKR Framework

    • The Sandboxing Framework

    • Aligning Missions, Goals and Results

    • Task Prioritization Techniques

    • Running Effective Meetings: Amazons Two Pizzas Rule

    • Understand and Combating the HIPPO Effect

    • Creating Time for Thinking: Lessons from Jeff Bezos and Eric Schmidt

    • Becoming a Heat Shield

    • Overcoming the Imposter Syndrome

    • The Anti-Complex Framework

  4. 04

    Sales &Negotiation

    9 modules
    20 lessons

    For entrepreneurs, mastering sales and negotiation techniques is essential. This module is designed to equip any entrepreneur with the tools to grow their business through sales.

    This module covers:


    • Discovering the Buying Motives

    • The Trusted Adviser Posture

    • Risk Reversal

    • The Two Types of Questions

    • The Power of Attitude

    • Being Assertive vs. Patient

    • Using the Voice of Customers

    • Mastering the Pitch

    • Personal Brand Building

  5. 05

    Business Operations
    8 modules
    20 lessons

    How do Businesses actually run? It 's all about the operations. In this module, you 'll learn how to make the different pieces of the puzzle work together.

    This module covers:

    • Processing Customer Feedback

    • Navigating through Crises: Lessons from Lime

    • Forging Business Partnerships

    • The Rules of Expansion

    • Organic vs. Inorganic Growth

    • Community Building: Wikipedias Playbook

    • Defining Company Values

    • The Friction Reduction Framework

    • Building a Premium Brand

    • Authentic Branding

  6. 06

    Management
    5 modules
    20 lessons

    This module explores key management concepts and techniques to help entrepreneurs move their company forward.

    This module covers:

    • The Science Behind Motivation

    • Making Hard Decisions

    • Mentorship &Sponsorship

    • The Massive Transformative Purpose

    • Alignment: Lessons from YouTube

    • Combating the Halo Effect

    • Hiring and Onboarding Principles

    • Diversity and Inclusion

    • Bonuses and Promotions

    • The Rules of Professional Success

  7. 07

    Financial Accounting
    5 modules
    20 lessons

    No business education is complete without a robust knowledge of Financial Accounting. In this module, youll learn to interpret and manage financial information, a crucial skill for making informed business decisions.

    This module covers:

    • Financial vs. Managerial Accounting

    • The Accounting Equation

    • The Three Financial Statements

    • Understanding the Income Statement

    • Assessing Company Health

    • Breaking Down Liabilities

    • Cash Inflows and Outflows

    • Financial Ratios

Frequently Asked Questions

  • I work full-time, is this program for me?

    Yes, most of our students work full-time. Thats why weve designed our programs to be completely online and self-paced.

  • How long does the Augment MBA Program take to complete?

    The Augment MBA is self-paced, so completion times vary. Most students take between 2 and 6 months to finish the program.

  • What is the program price?

    The Augment MBA in Entrepreneurship is priced at $1,750. Augment offers financial aid to highly motivated individuals who lack the financial resources to access the program. To apply, please contact us at: team@augment.school.

  • Is Augment just video lessons?

    No. Our program also include quizzes, case studies, written assignments, and downloadable handbooks.

  • Is Augment accredited?

    No, and we have no intention of seeking accreditation. We do however provide finishers with a LinkedIn certificate, signed by Chris Barton, the Founder of Shazam.

  • Does Augment offer financial aid?

    Augment offers financial aid to highly motivated individuals who lack the financial resources to access our program. To apply, please contact us at team@augment.school.

  • Does Augment offer networking opportunities?

    Yes! By enrolling in our program, youlljoin a vibrant global community of ambitious entrepreneurs. The community consists of an in-house platform, a LinkedIn group, as well as weekly virtual and in-person events.

  • Can I get a refund if Im not satisfied?

    Yes. All students are eligible for a full refund within 15 days of enrollment - no questions asked.

  • Does Augment offer team plans?

    Yes. For team inquiries, contact us directly at team@augment.school.
